snippet.textDisplay: People are trashing this song saying its too "Indianised" and Naseebo should have sung a Punjabi song and not Rajasthani (Cholisthani), I say bullshit. Someone like me, with no professional music knowledge, having heard Naseebo for the first time (see I dont have any benchmark), I thought she just nailed it, her rustic voice was so amazing to listen to, and Umair complemented her beautifully. And my faith in Coke Studio Pakistan keeps growing, they can never do anything substandard.
